name: Cholera
description: Cholera is an acute diarrheal illness caused by infection of the intestine with the bacterium Vibrio cholerae. Cholera is transmitted through contaminated food and water. Symptoms include watery diarrhea, vomiting, and leg cramps. Severe cases can lead to dehydration and death if not treated promptly.

name: Rotavirus enteritis
description: Rotavirus enteritis is an acute diarrheal illness caused by infection of the intestine with the rotavirus. Rotavirus is transmitted through contaminated food and water. Symptoms include watery diarrhea, vomiting, and fever. Severe cases can lead to dehydration and death if not treated promptly.

name: Human Immunodeficiency Virus (HIV) disease
description: Human Immunodeficiency Virus (HIV) disease is a chronic viral infection that attacks the immune system. HIV is transmitted through contact with infected blood, semen, vaginal fluids, or breast milk. Symptoms include fever, fatigue, weight loss, and swollen lymph nodes. Severe cases can lead to acquired immunodeficiency syndrome (AIDS) if not treated promptly.

name: Iron deficiency anemia
description: Iron deficiency anemia is a condition in which the body lacks sufficient iron to produce hemoglobin. Iron deficiency anemia is caused by inadequate dietary intake of iron, blood loss, and malabsorption of iron. Symptoms include fatigue, weakness, pale skin, and shortness of breath. Severe cases can lead to heart failure if not treated promptly.

name: Hereditary hemochromatosis
description: Hereditary hemochromatosis is a genetic disorder that causes the body to absorb too much iron from the diet. Hereditary hemochromatosis is caused by mutations in the HFE gene. Symptoms include fatigue, joint pain, abdominal pain, and skin pigmentation. Severe cases can lead to liver cirrhosis, heart failure, and diabetes if not treated promptly.

Generalized anxiety disorder is caused by genetic factors, hormonal factors, and environmental factors. Symptoms include restlessness, irritability, muscle tension, and sleep disturbances. name: Osteoporosis with pathological fracture
description: Osteoporosis is a metabolic bone disorder that causes decreased bone density and increased risk of fractures. Severe cases can lead to disability and death if not treated promptly.

name: Osteoarthritis of the knee
description: Osteoarthritis is a degenerative joint disorder that causes pain, stiffness, and swelling in the affected joint. Osteoarthritis is caused by aging, obesity, and joint injury.
